Faculty/ Faculties
(when referring to the teachers)

Let's Understand: The term faculty (when referring to teachers) can be used in both singular and plural forms for one organization. However, when you want to refer to the pool of teachers from multiple organizations, you can use faculties.
Please note that the term faculty has some more meanings attached to it. Click here to know more.

Incorrect Usages: The faculties of KIET Group of Institutions are erudite.
                            : The faculty of IIT-R and IIT-B will visit KIET Group of Institutions.

Correct Usages: The faculty of KIET Group of Institutions are erudite.
                            : The faculties of IIT-R and IIT-B will visit KIET Group of Institutions.
